1:03:41.313 --> 1:03:43.106
What?

1:03:43.106 --> 1:03:48.070
Me, no um I would never mess with...

1:03:48.111 --> 1:03:51.572
You ever took a poke at creative endeavors?
[SALEEM] No!

1:03:51.572 --> 1:03:53.157
not really.

1:03:53.157 --> 1:03:55.910
You ever penetrate unexpected places?
[SALEEM] No!

1:03:55.910 --> 1:03:58.287
No.

1:03:58.828 --> 1:04:00.456
Well you should!

1:04:00.664 --> 1:04:03.083
Me and the misses

1:04:03.875 --> 1:04:07.879
try to visit somewhere new every year.

1:04:11.840 --> 1:04:15.803
Yes. I did that.

1:04:15.803 --> 1:04:17.389
I did that.

1:04:17.389 --> 1:04:19.807
Merry Christmas my dear.

1:04:19.807 --> 1:04:21.934
And Merry Christmas to you Aunty.

1:04:21.934 --> 1:04:24.937
For a second I thought I broke into the wrong house.

1:04:24.937 --> 1:04:26.355
Oh don’t worry about them.

1:04:26.355 --> 1:04:29.358
Plenty more where they came from.

1:04:32.360 --> 1:04:36.990
And these three terrors are Alia,

1:04:37.614 --> 1:04:40.033
Fasia... Frida...

1:04:40.033 --> 1:04:40.867
Anyway,

1:04:40.867 --> 1:04:46.665
if their mother would actually come by with them more often
to visit, this wouldn't happen.

1:04:46.665 --> 1:04:48.624
Anyway don't let me bore you.

1:04:48.624 --> 1:04:56.215
Let's go to the kitchen where all the action is.

1:05:07.976 --> 1:05:11.938
Aziza, don’t let them fellas whip you all again you know.

1:05:11.938 --> 1:05:14.941
We will never hear the end of it.

1:05:16.192 --> 1:05:20.779
And fellas don't cheat, I'm watching you all.

1:05:21.071 --> 1:05:23.991
Well Saleem

1:05:23.991 --> 1:05:30.830
this beauty here is my wife for almost three thirty years.

1:05:30.830 --> 1:05:32.207
Hi, nice to meet you.

1:05:32.207 --> 1:05:34.208
Nice to meet you Saleem

1:05:34.208 --> 1:05:39.213
And sitting to her right is her mother Elizabeth,

1:05:39.839 --> 1:05:43.301
It's Mama to you and me.

1:05:43.593 --> 1:05:46.596
Now who am I forgetting

1:05:55.686 --> 1:05:58.773
So the famous Saleem.

1:05:58.773 --> 1:06:00.191
Hey man. Nice to...

1:06:00.191 --> 1:06:02.068
Ah Big step?

1:06:02.068 --> 1:06:05.029
The first family gathering.

1:06:05.029 --> 1:06:05.613
I guess.

1:06:05.613 --> 1:06:08.157
You are not what I was expecting to be honest.

1:06:08.157 --> 1:06:10.825
The way she described you.
[PETER] Luke.

1:06:10.825 --> 1:06:12.411
Be nice.

1:06:12.411 --> 1:06:16.164
It’s okay. It’s okay uncle.

1:06:16.164 --> 1:06:18.875
Just introducing myself to Saleem.

1:06:18.875 --> 1:06:22.504
Have to look out for my baby cousin is all.

1:06:23.421 --> 1:06:27.007
There’s nothing like family,

1:06:27.007 --> 1:06:29.259
am I right Saleem?

1:06:29.259 --> 1:06:30.803
Yeah.

1:06:30.803 --> 1:06:32.845
Yes.

1:06:33.138 --> 1:06:35.224
Anyway,

1:06:35.224 --> 1:06:38.226
I think I will finish this off yonder.

1:06:39.852 --> 1:06:41.521
There is nothing

1:06:41.521 --> 1:06:44.649
like fresh air in your lungs

1:06:44.649 --> 1:06:49.487
While sucking on the teet of nature's best vino.

1:06:54.950 --> 1:06:57.953
c'est magnifique

1:07:06.335 --> 1:07:08.295
I'm sorry about that.

1:07:08.295 --> 1:07:11.298
That's my sister's kid.

1:07:11.298 --> 1:07:12.841
It's okay.

1:07:12.841 --> 1:07:18.471
She gets to fly god knows where with her new...

1:07:19.139 --> 1:07:21.474
Anyway.

1:07:21.474 --> 1:07:25.811
Saleem, please take a seat.

1:07:40.032 --> 1:07:41.452
Hi aunty.

1:07:41.452 --> 1:07:43.244
Nice to meet you.

1:07:43.244 --> 1:07:45.288
Hello Grace.

1:07:45.288 --> 1:07:50.876
I’m glad you could make it to our little get together.

1:07:53.754 --> 1:07:56.256
Can I help with anything?

1:07:58.300 --> 1:08:00.218
Of course.

1:08:01.219 --> 1:08:02.928
Join the line.

1:09:14.411 --> 1:09:18.415
Pete, you need some help? Please.

1:09:18.415 --> 1:09:21.627
It’s alright Saleem,

1:09:21.627 --> 1:09:23.754
Just going to use the bathroom.

1:09:23.754 --> 1:09:26.756
Thankfully that is a solo department for now.

1:09:37.850 --> 1:09:41.435
Your Ecarte is very good Mrs. Samuel.

1:09:41.435 --> 1:09:43.604
Actually it’s an En Pointe,

1:09:43.604 --> 1:09:46.608
but I’m impressed a young man even noticed.

1:09:49.318 --> 1:09:52.738
Sorry. Excuse me.

1:09:59.829 --> 1:10:01.330
Were you involved in dance?

1:10:01.330 --> 1:10:04.457
Oh no. Not the men in my family.

1:10:04.457 --> 1:10:07.377
But my sister was quite good.

1:10:07.377 --> 1:10:11.172
Yea she really took to the contemporary style of ballet.

1:10:11.172 --> 1:10:12.549
Me too!

1:10:12.549 --> 1:10:13.800
Does she still practice?

1:10:13.800 --> 1:10:17.219
No, unfortunately not.

1:10:17.219 --> 1:10:19.513
She spent most of her life practicing it

1:10:19.513 --> 1:10:22.516
Then she just stopped. Normal for Abeerah I guess.

1:10:22.516 --> 1:10:25.143
Well she got further than my Gracey.

1:10:25.143 --> 1:10:29.648
Lord she would scream and scream.

1:10:29.648 --> 1:10:33.861
I truly believe that she learnt to walk just to run away
from the studio

1:10:33.861 --> 1:10:36.862
Sounds like Grace.

1:10:38.071 --> 1:10:41.074
She really is strong headed isn’t she?

1:10:42.284 --> 1:10:44.829
It’s a good quality.

1:10:44.952 --> 1:10:47.956
Speaking of, where..?

1:10:49.625 --> 1:10:53.294
Sorry, I’m just going to take this really quickly.

1:10:53.294 --> 1:10:56.297
Where’s your washroom?
[FIONA] It's around the corner.

1:10:59.300 --> 1:11:00.593
Hey.

1:11:00.593 --> 1:11:01.927
Where the fuck are you?!

1:11:01.927 --> 1:11:03.888
I’m here.

1:11:03.888 --> 1:11:07.264
You’re not here, cause I’m fucking here

1:11:07.264 --> 1:11:11.144
with your army of, I’m sorry, but super mean aunties, and
you’re nowhere to be seen.

1:11:11.144 --> 1:11:13.605
Wait, you’re by my house?

1:11:13.605 --> 1:11:16.316
Yes Saleem! How slow are you driving?

1:11:16.316 --> 1:11:19.318
I’m by your family now.

1:11:19.443 --> 1:11:20.779
Why?!

1:11:20.779 --> 1:11:22.529
That was the plan.

1:11:22.529 --> 1:11:25.366
How the hell was that the plan?

1:11:25.366 --> 1:11:26.991
You said pull the bandaid.

1:11:26.991 --> 1:11:27.743
Your words.

1:11:27.743 --> 1:11:30.412
That makes no sense.

1:11:30.412 --> 1:11:32.163
It kind of does.

1:11:33.582 --> 1:11:36.835
Just get your ass here before I look even worse!

1:11:37.377 --> 1:11:38.920
I’m sure you’re freaking out too.
[SALEEM] Well

1:11:38.920 --> 1:11:41.422
actually your dad has been really nice,

1:11:41.422 --> 1:11:44.842
OH, and your mom, she likes me so...

1:11:46.050 --> 1:11:49.054
But you are right, be there soon.

1:11:49.054 --> 1:11:50.889
You better.

1:12:10.574 --> 1:12:12.242
There you are.

1:12:12.242 --> 1:12:14.577
Can you help me with something?

1:12:14.577 --> 1:12:16.329
Well actually I just got off the phone with Grace...

1:12:16.329 --> 1:12:18.665
Okay great.

1:12:39.934 --> 1:12:42.937
There’s nothing like these,

1:12:44.480 --> 1:12:45.898
do you want a taste?

1:12:45.898 --> 1:12:47.817
Really takes you back to those wide open plains.

1:12:47.817 --> 1:12:50.318
Yea thanks.

1:12:50.318 --> 1:12:55.157
Actually no. Not sure why I said that. I don’t smoke.

1:12:56.992 --> 1:12:59.286
I respect that.

1:12:59.286 --> 1:13:03.623
A man has to live long enough to take care of his kin.

1:13:10.296 --> 1:13:12.423
You work with your hands a lot?

1:13:12.423 --> 1:13:14.759
Yeah, woodworking.

1:13:14.759 --> 1:13:16.886
Good.

1:13:16.886 --> 1:13:19.262
Good.

1:13:21.014 --> 1:13:25.434
Yeah. I miss those days.

1:13:25.434 --> 1:13:29.396
when men weren't afraid to be men, you know?

1:13:29.939 --> 1:13:35.152
Building, hunting, et cetera.

1:13:35.152 --> 1:13:36.110
et cetera.

1:13:36.110 --> 1:13:38.196
you do any woodworking or anything like that?

1:13:38.196 --> 1:13:40.741
Me? God no!

1:13:45.077 --> 1:13:47.663
I am...

1:13:47.663 --> 1:13:50.666
I’m an accountant.

1:13:51.249 --> 1:13:52.877
But those were the days,

1:13:52.877 --> 1:13:54.045
Yeah.

1:13:54.544 --> 1:13:57.547
men being men.

1:13:57.714 --> 1:13:59.716
men being men.

1:14:10.684 --> 1:14:12.228
Grace.

1:14:12.228 --> 1:14:16.023
could you please take this to the dining room.

1:14:16.023 --> 1:14:17.066
Sure.

1:14:17.066 --> 1:14:20.193
place it just to the left of the beef ham,

1:14:20.193 --> 1:14:21.611
but not too close,

1:14:21.611 --> 1:14:24.073
oh!, and leave room for the salad,

1:14:24.073 --> 1:14:26.657
That goes right after the rice.

1:14:26.657 --> 1:14:29.661
Okay, I think I got it.

1:15:07.236 --> 1:15:08.822
Hello.

1:15:09.446 --> 1:15:12.449
Oh I’m really sorry.

1:15:12.616 --> 1:15:16.662
Is this the West Indies tour of England of umm... 1984?

1:15:16.662 --> 1:15:19.205
Yes, yes it is.

1:15:19.205 --> 1:15:21.041
Who are you?

1:15:21.500 --> 1:15:25.420
Grace, I’m really sorry for the interrupt.

1:15:25.420 --> 1:15:27.463
The Grace?

1:15:27.463 --> 1:15:29.340
I’m a Grace, yes.

1:15:29.340 --> 1:15:33.177
Please put that down before your arms break off.

1:15:33.177 --> 1:15:33.969
Thanks.

1:15:33.969 --> 1:15:38.057
Not sure how much longer I could have lasted.

1:15:38.057 --> 1:15:41.268
A lot of mouths to feed out there.

1:15:41.268 --> 1:15:45.271
My wife does tend to prepare for an army.

1:15:45.689 --> 1:15:48.901
Oh my god, very nice to meet you.

1:15:50.484 --> 1:15:53.030
[MUSTAPHA] Come on!
[GRACE] Hurts every time!

1:15:53.821 --> 1:15:56.574
Please sit, sit.

1:15:58.282 --> 1:16:03.330
So, how you making out in the trenches?

1:16:13.380 --> 1:16:15.257
Um, Peter,

1:16:15.257 --> 1:16:17.010
Sorry. I mean Pete.

1:16:17.010 --> 1:16:18.302
What’s that Saleem?

1:16:18.302 --> 1:16:21.889
Should we be heading back in? Maybe they need some help or..

1:16:21.889 --> 1:16:23.307
No.

1:16:25.391 --> 1:16:26.602
No.

1:16:28.187 --> 1:16:31.190
Let the women gab for a bit longer.

1:16:36.235 --> 1:16:39.237
You do know you’re the first she’s brought home?

1:16:42.116 --> 1:16:43.993
No she...

1:16:43.993 --> 1:16:44.826
Well...

1:16:44.826 --> 1:16:46.745
She said she wasn’t new to this whole

1:16:46.745 --> 1:16:48.205
bringing home boys

1:16:48.205 --> 1:16:51.750
Not like she’s been with man a lot of... Plenty umm

1:16:51.750 --> 1:16:54.044
It’s okay Saleem.

1:16:54.543 --> 1:16:57.546
I know my Gracey is not perfect.

1:16:58.673 --> 1:16:59.924
Right.

1:17:00.549 --> 1:17:04.053
Beauty of her mother and head like father's.

1:17:08.514 --> 1:17:09.724
Yeah.

1:17:11.184 --> 1:17:14.980
But I have noticed a change in her over the last few months.

1:17:18.191 --> 1:17:18.900
Yeah?

1:17:18.900 --> 1:17:20.026
Yeah.

1:17:21.610 --> 1:17:24.612
There’s a calmness to her now.

1:17:27.241 --> 1:17:29.409
You make her happy,

1:17:30.368 --> 1:17:32.788
and I’m happy for that.

1:17:32.788 --> 1:17:34.621
Thanks Pete.

1:17:37.458 --> 1:17:39.127
And listen.

1:17:47.718 --> 1:17:53.389
I don’t have to express what happens if
her happiness should suddenly

1:17:53.389 --> 1:17:55.391
expires do I?

1:17:55.391 --> 1:17:58.769
No I understand.

1:18:00.855 --> 1:18:03.983
And if I know my little Gracey, she can be
a real firecracker.

1:18:03.983 --> 1:18:04.984
Yea,

1:18:04.984 --> 1:18:11.323
Grace, she can handle herself anywhere.

1:18:18.163 --> 1:18:19.873
Great match.

1:18:19.873 --> 1:18:22.374
The best match.

1:18:24.127 --> 1:18:27.421
Still quiet out there.

1:18:27.421 --> 1:18:30.799
May have time for some highlights.

1:18:31.925 --> 1:18:35.594
What about... the match.

1:18:35.594 --> 1:18:38.723
Which 'The match' are you speaking about exactly.

1:18:38.723 --> 1:18:41.017
What else uncle? Lara.

1:18:41.017 --> 1:18:42.434
Best there ever was!

1:18:42.434 --> 1:18:45.063
So young, so so wrong.

1:18:45.063 --> 1:18:47.023
Come on OLD MAN.

1:18:47.023 --> 1:18:47.940
Ahhh.

1:18:47.940 --> 1:18:50.817
There are matches past the 1980s you know.

1:18:50.817 --> 1:18:54.737
Won by players born after those games were long done.

1:18:54.737 --> 1:18:56.531
True but

1:18:56.531 --> 1:18:59.117
tapes are expensive

1:18:59.117 --> 1:19:01.660
and why waste money on that.

1:19:01.660 --> 1:19:06.291
You know, Saleem is always a generation
behind on everything but

1:19:06.291 --> 1:19:08.626
even he doesn't use tapes anymore.

1:19:08.626 --> 1:19:11.629
Ahh Saleem.

1:19:11.670 --> 1:19:14.589
Always right on time,

1:19:14.589 --> 1:19:20.678
even when I begged him to just hold on one more day.

1:19:20.678 --> 1:19:23.681
Right 84!

1:19:23.681 --> 1:19:24.974
Good year to be born,

1:19:24.974 --> 1:19:26.101
cricket wise.

1:19:26.101 --> 1:19:27.769
Great year for me.

1:19:27.769 --> 1:19:29.228
I became a man.

1:19:29.228 --> 1:19:30.978
‘I became a man’.

1:19:30.978 --> 1:19:32.398
It’s true.

1:19:32.398 --> 1:19:36.735
Freshly married, first real job,

1:19:37.111 --> 1:19:40.655
And Saleem came into our lives

1:19:40.655 --> 1:19:44.909
made us a family.

1:20:01.591 --> 1:20:02.884
Well Saleem,

1:20:02.884 --> 1:20:04.761
that sound tells me it’s that time.

1:20:04.761 --> 1:20:05.929
Lets dig in.

1:20:05.929 --> 1:20:07.638
Be right with you.

1:20:07.638 --> 1:20:10.641
I want to check on Grace again.

1:20:11.058 --> 1:20:12.643
Good man.

1:20:55.349 --> 1:20:59.353
Hey I thought I was supposed to meet you at my house.

1:21:01.605 --> 1:21:02.689
Ouch.

1:21:02.689 --> 1:21:03.523
You left me!

1:21:03.523 --> 1:21:05.150
You hit me... Hard

1:21:05.150 --> 1:21:06.651
Yes, yes I did.

1:21:06.651 --> 1:21:07.736
And I did not leave you.

1:21:07.736 --> 1:21:11.323
Okay okay. Let’s agree... mistakes were made.

1:21:11.323 --> 1:21:12.115
Yes.

1:21:12.115 --> 1:21:13.824
How was it?

1:21:15.117 --> 1:21:16.869
That bad?

1:21:16.869 --> 1:21:18.037
I met your dad.

1:21:18.037 --> 1:21:19.288
Yeah?

1:21:19.288 --> 1:21:20.623
And your mom.

1:21:20.623 --> 1:21:22.166
Oh.

1:21:22.665 --> 1:21:25.668
But I figure they make a good balance.

1:21:26.085 --> 1:21:29.088
So tell me, how terrible was your day?

1:21:29.088 --> 1:21:32.675
Not terrible. I was quite the charmer if I do say so myself.

1:21:32.675 --> 1:21:34.177
Do I have to hit you again?

1:21:34.177 --> 1:21:37.596
Won’t change the fact that I hit it off with your parents.

1:21:37.596 --> 1:21:39.307
Both of them.

1:21:39.389 --> 1:21:40.724
Mummy too?

1:21:40.724 --> 1:21:44.186
Yea! Just talked about ballet, you know, the usual.

1:21:44.186 --> 1:21:45.728
You sly devil.

1:21:45.728 --> 1:21:48.398
You said it, not me.

1:21:48.398 --> 1:21:49.898
[GRACE] Anyway.
[SALEEM] One more thing.

1:21:49.898 --> 1:21:51.026
What's that?

1:21:51.026 --> 1:21:53.736
Your cousin. He’s...

1:21:53.736 --> 1:21:57.615
What? Luke. He's the best.

1:21:57.615 --> 1:22:01.285
Yeah. He really did not um, like me there?

1:22:01.285 --> 1:22:03.995
No. He’s just being protective.

1:22:03.995 --> 1:22:05.414
Well he...

1:22:05.414 --> 1:22:09.291
When we were kids we used to say we would get married.

1:22:13.838 --> 1:22:16.091
So what’s the plan now?

1:22:16.091 --> 1:22:18.717
We go back?

1:22:19.552 --> 1:22:21.929
We go to your place?

1:22:21.929 --> 1:22:23.556
Well we cant stay here.

1:22:23.556 --> 1:22:26.558
Oh just shut up.
